[By far, the largest use of phosphoric acid is in the production of
fertilizers. Toxic effects on animals, including humans, comes from
inhalation and affects the respiratory system. The vet might be
referring to rat poisons containing phosphorus. Animals intoxicated
with this kind of poison present a locomotion disorder (staggering),
vomiting, and diarrhea. Symptoms may include pain in the abdomen and
convulsions.

A map of Neuchatel is available at http://healthmap.org/r/1AFu. -
Mod.PMB]
